Q2.	A) Create three directory a b and c and create a.txt,b.txt and c.txt
		in each directory respectively and then copy c directory into the a.
	B)Move Directory b to c.
	C)Create alias of ls -lh command to your name.
	D)Change Directory name a to cdac.

ans>	A)	vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ mkdir a
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ mkdir b
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ mkdir c

		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/a$ cat > a.txt
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/a$ cat > b.txt
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/a$ cat > c.txt

		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/b$ cat > a.txt
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/b$ cat > b.txt
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/b$ cat > c.txt

		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/c$ cat > a.txt
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/c$ cat > b.txt
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/c$ cat > c.txt

		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ mv c a

		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/a$ ls
		a.txt  b.txt  c  c.txt

	B)	vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ mv b a
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ cd a	

		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/a$ mv b c
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/a$ cd c
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/a/c$ ls
		a.txt  b  b.txt  c.txt

	C)	vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ ls -lh
		total 8.0K
		drwxr-xr-x 3 vikas vikas 4.0K Sep  8 18:13 a
		drwxr-xr-x 2 vikas vikas 4.0K Sep  8 18:05 c

	D)	vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ mv a cdac
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ ls
		c  cdac

