Q3. A) Create five files file1.txt , file2.txt ,file3.txt file4.txt and
    file5.txt with some text inside it. Search for 's' character
    inside all the files using grep command.
    Also Use cat to view all file content together.
	B)Create file.txt using cat and edit that using nano editor.
	c)Create 5 empty files using touch command
	D)Remove previously created directory a , b and c.

ans>	A)	vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ cat > file1.txt
		file1 sno 1
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ cat > file2.txt
		file2 sno 2
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ cat > file3.txt
		file3 sno 3
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ cat > file4.txt
		file4 sno 4
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ cat > file5.txt
		file5 sno 5
		
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ grep s file1.txt file2.txt file3.txt file4.txt file5.txt 
		file1.txt:file1 sno 1
		file2.txt:file2 sno 2
		file3.txt:file3 sno 3
		file4.txt:file4 sno 4
		file5.txt:file5 sno 5

	B)	vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ cat > file.txt
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ nano file.txt

	C)	vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ touch f1.txt	
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ touch f2.txt
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ touch f3.txt
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ touch f4.txt
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ touch f5.txt

	D)	vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ rmdir c
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/cdac/c$ rmdir b
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS/cdac$ rmdir c
		vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ rmdir cdac



