Q1. Create directory of your name and then create 4 files inside it named
	a.txt, b.txt, c.txt and d.sh. And change the directory permission to
	only user and also files permission to only user such that
		a)user can read and write the file a.txt and b.txt
		b)user can write the file c.txt
		c)user can exectuable the file d.sh. Make
			Contents of file d.sh:
			#/bin/sh
			ls -lh

ans>	vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ mkdir vikas
	
	vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ touch a.txt b.txt c.txt

	a) vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ chmod +rw a.txt b.txt

	b) vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ chmod +w c.txt

	c) vikas@vikas-Aspire-E5-574G:~/OS$ cat > d.sh
	   #/bin/sh
	   chmod +x d.sh

